==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: mated
<hw>mated</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Brought together for
sexual activity; bred; -- of animals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Sorted into pairs of identical size, color, or other
properties; -- used of gloves, socks, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> paired.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Same as <er>married</er>. Opposite of
<ant>unmarried</ant>; <as>as, they were a devoted couple, <ex>mated</ex>
for life</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Matelasse</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
